        "body": "## Stack Refresh\n\nRestacked on #84340 after the Doctor note policy simplification.\n\nCurrent parent: #84340 (`doctor-gateway-services-structured-repairs`).\nCurrent head is a single commit on top of that parent.\n\n## Contract Notes\n\nThis PR follows the refreshed structured Doctor contract:\n\n```ts\ndetect(ctx, scope?) -> HealthFinding[]\nrepair(ctx, findings) -> HealthRepairResult\n```\n\nFindings are machine/CI/lint signal. Human presentation uses `ctx.doctor.note(message, title?)` when needed; this PR keeps session repair reporting in findings/effects/changes/warnings.\n\n## Scope\n\nConverts session lock and session transcript repairs to structured detection, scoped mutation, dry-run output, and detect-after validation.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Restacked on refreshed #84340.\n- Confirmed by code search that this branch does not reintroduce `HealthPresentationNote`, `repairNote`, `detectionNotes`, `repairNotes`, or structured note result surfaces.\n- No focused test rerun completed in this local worktree; use fresh CI for broad proof.\r\n",
